<bioghist>
<head>Biography</head>
<p>Sir Jacob Epstein (1880-1959) was a major modernist sculptor best known for his portraits. He was born in New York but as a young man became a citizen of the United Kingdom, living in that country for the remainder of his life. As attested to by this collection's contents, he once visited the Silvermine group of artists at the High Perch Farm in the Silvermine district of Wilton, New Canaan, and Norwalk, Conn.</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent>
<head>Scope and Content of Collection</head>
<p>The Jacob Epstein Collection contains photographs of Jacob Epstein, his art, and unidentified people at Raspit Hill, Kent, United Kingdom and High Perch Farm, Silvermine, Conn.</p>
</scopecontent>
